      %span.name next siblings
      selector
    .entry-details
      %h4.name
        %span.versionAdded>
          version added:
          %a{:href => "/version/1.0/"} 1.0
        jQuery('prev ~ siblings')
      %ul.signatures
        %li
          %dl.arguments
            %dt prev
            %dd Any valid selector.
            %dt siblings
            %dd A selector to filter elements that are the following siblings of the first selector.
      %p.desc
        %strong> Description:
        Selects all sibling elements that follow after the "prev" element, have the same parent, and match the filtering "siblings" selector.
      .longdesc
        %p
          The notable difference between (
          %code> prev + next
          ) and (
          %code> prev ~ siblings
          ) is their respective reach. While the former reaches only to the immediately following sibling element, the latter extends that reach to all following sibling elements.
      %h3 Example:
      #entry-examples.entry-examples
        #example-0
          %h4
            %span.desc Finds all divs that are siblings after the element with #prev as its id.  Notice the span isn't selected since it is not a div and the "niece" isn't selected since it is a child of a sibling, not an actual sibling.
          %pre
            %code.example.demo-code
              :preserve
